==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bollworm
<hw>Boll"worm`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The larva of a moth (<spn>Heliothis armigera</spn>) which devours
the bolls or unripe pods of the cotton plant, often doing great damage
to the crops.</def> <-- <spn>Heliothis zea</spn> ?? = cotton bollworm,
corn earworm, tomato fuitworm ?? -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Boln</ent>⟦br⟧
